<subSubSection id="48D355CA8EA6FF2848A7544DFE2BFB11" pageId="232" pageNumber="233" type="description">
<paragraph id="007606418EA6FF2848A7544DFBC6FB4D" blockId="232.[151,1437,865,1430]" pageId="232" pageNumber="233">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538EA6FF2848A7544DFE0FFC89" bold="true" box="[151,426,865,890]" pageId="232" pageNumber="233">Description of Female.</emphasis>
Fully winged; length 
<quantity id="C731ABA48EA6FF284A81544DFC98FC89" box="[689,829,865,889]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.65" metricValueMax="3.9" metricValueMin="3.4" pageId="232" pageNumber="233" unit="mm" value="3.65" valueMax="3.9" valueMin="3.4">3.4–3.9 mm</quantity>
. Head black; antenna brown, except segments 1–2 or 1–3 yellow; mesosoma and metasoma black; legs yellow. Antenna clavate. Head dull, hairy, slightly granulated and reticulate rugose; areas on sides of ocelli not reticulate rugose; occipital carina complete; ocellar triangle equilateral; mandible quadridentate, with one rudimentary tooth between two posterior teeth. Scutum shiny, hairy, granulated, reticulate rugose near anterior margin. Notauli complete, posteriorly separated. Scutellum shiny, hairy, punctate, reticulate rugose near posterior margin, about twice as long as metanotum. Metanotum reticulate rugose. Propodeum reticulate rugose; posterior surface with two complete longitudinal keels. Fore wing with one dark transverse band; stigmal vein slightly curved (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48EA6FF284AAE5371FCA9FB85" box="[670,780,1117,1141]" captionStart="PLATE 65" captionStartId="224.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[222,1389,239,1814]" captionTargetId="figure-78@224.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="224" captionText="PLATE 65. A, E. Chelae, holotypes. B, C. Stigmal veins. D. Male genitalia, holotype. A. Bocchus haladai (from Olmi 2008b). B, D. B. indicus, male (from Olmi 1987a). C, E. B. laotianus, female (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.18 mm for A, 0.35 mm for B and C, 0.23 mm for D and 0.18 mm for E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278601" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278601/files/figure.png" pageId="232" pageNumber="233">Plate 65C</figureCitation>
); pterostigma short and narrow. Protarsal segments 
<quantity id="C731ABA48EA6FF284D655371FA39FB85" box="[1365,1436,1117,1141]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.35" metricValueMax="10.16" metricValueMin="2.54" pageId="232" pageNumber="233" unit="in" value="2.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="1.0">1–4 in</quantity>
following proportions: 20:3:3:14. Enlarged claw (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48EA6FF284AFA53ADFC92FB69" box="[714,823,1153,1177]" captionStart="PLATE 65" captionStartId="224.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[222,1389,239,1814]" captionTargetId="figure-78@224.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="224" captionText="PLATE 65. A, E. Chelae, holotypes. B, C. Stigmal veins. D. Male genitalia, holotype. A. Bocchus haladai (from Olmi 2008b). B, D. B. indicus, male (from Olmi 1987a). C, E. B. laotianus, female (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.18 mm for A, 0.35 mm for B and C, 0.23 mm for D and 0.18 mm for E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278601" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278601/files/figure.png" pageId="232" pageNumber="233">Plate 65E</figureCitation>
) with one row of ten teeth and one bristle. Segment 5 of protarsus (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48EA6FF28491C5389FE3DFB4D" box="[300,408,1189,1213]" captionStart="PLATE 65" captionStartId="224.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[222,1389,239,1814]" captionTargetId="figure-78@224.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="224" captionText="PLATE 65. A, E. Chelae, holotypes. B, C. Stigmal veins. D. Male genitalia, holotype. A. Bocchus haladai (from Olmi 2008b). B, D. B. indicus, male (from Olmi 1987a). C, E. B. laotianus, female (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.18 mm for A, 0.35 mm for B and C, 0.23 mm for D and 0.18 mm for E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278601" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278601/files/figure.png" pageId="232" pageNumber="233">Plate 65E</figureCitation>
) with one preapical lamella and two bristles. Tibial spurs 1/1/1.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418EA6FF2848F753E5FE2BFB11" blockId="232.[151,1437,865,1430]" box="[199,398,1225,1249]" pageId="232" pageNumber="233">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538EA6FF2848F753E5FEAEFB11" bold="true" box="[199,267,1225,1249]" pageId="232" pageNumber="233">Male.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
